Tracks:

Tracks made the last check up to his ship, it was rendered usless by 
the crashlanding. He sighed in desbilief "I better start looking for 
any lifesigns" Charging his black-light gun he headed straight into 
the jungle. His radars reading every small energy signature around. 
In spite of what he was expecting, something caught his attention, a 
faint signal. 
"What is this? I can't identify this energy signature!" He was 
growing neervous and activated every sensitive servo in her 
body. "Slag! Whatever it is, it's a hostile signal." The blue 
Corvette hid behind a large tree, hoping his enemy wouldn't be 
interested in deactivate him. "Where in the name of Cybertron I am?!"
